---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof vs Notion for Testimonials — There's a Better Way | SocialProof" description="Notion is great for docs and wikis. It's not built to collect and display testimonials on your website. SocialProof is — and it's free to start." canonical="https://socialproof.dev/vs/notion">
<style>
    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; margin: 0; background: #fff; color: #111; }
    nav { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: 1rem 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; }
    nav a.logo { font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #111; text-decoration: none; }
    nav .nav-links a { margin-left: 1.5rem; color: #555; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    nav .cta-nav { background: #111; color: #fff !important; padding: .45rem 1rem; border-radius: 6px; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .vs-badge { display: inline-block; background: #f0f0f0; color: #555; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: .35rem .75rem; border-radius: 99px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
    .hero h1 span { color: #4f46e5; }
    .hero p { font-size: 1.15rem; color: #444; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; }
    .hero-cta { display: inline-block; background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; padding: .85rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 1rem; }
    .hero-cta:hover { background: #3730a3; }
    section { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 2rem; }
    h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .compare-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .compare-table th { padding: .75rem 1rem; text-align: left; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .05em; color: #888; border-bottom: 2px solid #eee; }
    .compare-table th:nth-child(2) { color: #4f46e5; }
    .compare-table td { padding: .85rem 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0; font-size: 0.97rem; vertical-align: top; }
    .compare-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    .compare-table td:first-child { color: #555; font-weight: 500; }
    .yes { color: #16a34a; font-weight: 600; }
    .no { color: #dc2626; font-weight: 600; }
    .partial { color: #d97706; font-weight: 600; }
    .winner-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .winner-card { border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.75rem; }
    .winner-card.vouch { background: #f0fdf4; border: 1px solid #86efac; }
    .winner-card.other { background: #fafafa; border: 1px solid #e5e5e5; }
    .winner-card h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 .75rem; }
    .winner-card ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
    .winner-card li { font-size: 0.92rem; color: #444; margin-bottom: .4rem; }
    .insight-box { background: #f5f3ff; border: 1px solid #c4b5fd; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .insight-box h3 { margin: 0 0 .5rem; font-size: 1rem; }
    .insight-box p { margin: 0; color: #555; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .bottom-cta { text-align: center; background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; border-radius: 16px; padding: 3.5rem 2rem; margin: 3rem 0; }
    .bottom-cta h2 { color: #fff; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .bottom-cta p { opacity: .85; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .bottom-cta a { display: inline-block; background: #fff; color: #4f46e5; padding: .85rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; }
</style>

<nav>
  <a href="/" class="logo">SocialProof</a>
  <div class="nav-links">
    <a href="/for">Use cases</a>
    <a href="/vs">Compare</a>
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev" class="cta-nav">Try free →</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<div class="hero">
  <div class="vs-badge">SocialProof vs Notion</div>
  <h1>A Notion page of testimonials <span>isn't social proof</span></h1>
  <p>Pasting client quotes into a Notion doc doesn't convert visitors into customers. An embedded testimonial widget on your website does. Here's the difference.</p>
  <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev" class="hero-cta">Try SocialProof free →</a>
</div>

<section>
  <h2>The "Notion testimonials" pattern (and where it falls apart)</h2>
  <p style="color:#444;font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.7;">It usually starts well: you get a great review, paste it into Notion, maybe build a gallery view of client quotes. Some people link to it from their website. A few even embed their Notion page using an iframe.</p>
  <p style="color:#444;font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.7;">The problem? A Notion page full of testimonials requires visitors to leave your website to read them. And even embedded Notion looks like... Notion. Not like a trust signal that makes someone want to buy.</p>

  <div class="insight-box">
    <h3>🔑 The core issue</h3>
    <p>Testimonials work when they're embedded in the moment of decision — on your homepage, pricing page, or checkout. A linked Notion page breaks that flow. Visitors don't follow links to proof; they need to see it where they already are.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>What each tool actually does</h2>
  <table class="compare-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Feature</th>
        <th>SocialProof</th>
        <th>Notion</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Collect testimonials via shareable form</td>
        <td class="yes">✓ Branded, professional form</td>
        <td class="no">✗ Notion forms not meant for this</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Star ratings</td>
        <td class="yes">✓ Built-in</td>
        <td class="no">✗ Not a native feature</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Embeds inside your website</td>
        <td class="yes">✓ Native widget, 1 line of code</td>
        <td class="partial">⚠ Clunky iframe only</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Looks great on mobile</td>
        <td class="yes">✓ Responsive by default</td>
        <td class="no">✗ Notion embeds break on mobile</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Testimonial approval workflow</td>
        <td class="yes">✓ Review and approve before publishing</td>
        <td class="no">✗ Manual editing only</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Customer photos on testimonials</td>
        <td class="yes">✓ Submitters can upload photo</td>
        <td class="partial">⚠ Manual, no upload flow</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Designed for trust and conversion</td>
        <td class="yes">✓ Yes — this is the whole product</td>
        <td class="no">✗ Notion is for docs and wikis</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Free to start</td>
        <td class="yes">✓ Free forever for 1 widget</td>
        <td class="yes">✓ Free plan available</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Who should use what</h2>
  <div class="winner-grid">
    <div class="winner-card vouch">
      <h3>Use SocialProof if you…</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Want testimonials embedded on your actual website</li>
        <li>Need a professional collection form to send clients</li>
        <li>Want visitors to see proof without leaving your page</li>
        <li>Are a freelancer, coach, consultant, or small service business</li>
        <li>Need something that looks polished without design work</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="winner-card other">
      <h3>Keep using Notion if you…</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Just need a personal archive of positive feedback</li>
        <li>Are building an internal knowledge base that includes client quotes</li>
        <li>Use Notion as your primary workspace and just want a dump of praise</li>
        <li>Don't have a website to embed testimonials on</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Honest take</h2>
  <p style="color:#444;font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.7;">Notion is one of the most popular productivity tools on the planet, and for good reason. If you're using it to archive kind words from clients, that's fine — it's a great personal record.</p>
  <p style="color:#444;font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.7;">But if the goal is to <em>convert website visitors using social proof</em>, Notion isn't in the business. SocialProof is purpose-built for that: collect testimonials via a beautiful form, approve them, embed a responsive widget. Done.</p>
  <p style="color:#444;font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.7;">Free forever for 1 widget. No credit card required. Takes 5 minutes from signup to live widget.</p>

  <div class="bottom-cta">
    <h2>Put social proof where it converts.</h2>
    <p>Free forever for 1 active widget. No credit card. Embed on any website in minutes.</p>
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev">Start free →</a>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="footer-links" style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto 3rem;padding:1.5rem 2rem;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:0.9rem;">
  <strong style="color:#374151;">Also explore:</strong>
  <a href="/for/freelancers" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">For Freelancers</a>
  <a href="/for/coaches" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">For Coaches</a>
  <a href="/for/consultants" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">For Consultants</a>
  <a href="/vs/airtable" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">vs Airtable</a>
  <a href="/vs/typeform" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">vs Typeform</a>
  <a href="/vs/senja" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">vs Senja</a>
</div>
</Base>
